<div id="review_1425263937" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1425263937" />
    <a title="Anna Lumpkin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22025194-anna-lumpkin"><img alt="Anna Lumpkin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1565012215p2/22025194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1425263937?book_show_action=true">Jan 31, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna Lumpkin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna Lumpkin" href="/user/show/22025194-anna-lumpkin">Anna Lumpkin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22025194-anna-lumpkin?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22025194-anna-lumpkin?shelf=southern-lit">southern-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22025194-anna-lumpkin?shelf=she-wrote-it">she-wrote-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/22025194-anna-lumpkin?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1425263937" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16603021171212565174">&quot;The fact that my mother was moving so steadily toward middle age meant that my grandmother would soon have a grand companion, one more like herself. If my grandmother could’ve populated the world, all the people would’ve been women, and they all would’ve been just like her.&quot;<br/><br/>i dearly miss the relationships i used to have with my mom and nana - this book made me miss them even more. kaye gibbons is a true southern writer (like pat conroy) who can make me so happy and so sad at the same time. i lo</span>
  <span id="freeText16603021171212565174" style="display:none">"The fact that my mother was moving so steadily toward middle age meant that my grandmother would soon have a grand companion, one more like herself. If my grandmother could’ve populated the world, all the people would’ve been women, and they all would’ve been just like her."<br /><br />i dearly miss the relationships i used to have with my mom and nana - this book made me miss them even more. kaye gibbons is a true southern writer (like pat conroy) who can make me so happy and so sad at the same time. i loved, loved, loved this book. it's also so neat that the grandmother made the same trek i did- from morehead city to raleigh, nc. with references to the sanitary fish market and hayes barton pharmacy, gibbons just gets it. this will definitely be a re-read in the future for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16603021171212565174" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


